import plotly.graph_objects as go
import numpy as np

# Define x values
x = np.arange(0, 10, 0.01)

# Create figure
fig = go.Figure()

# Generate traces for all frequency-amplitude combinations
frequencies = np.arange(0.5, 5.5, 0.5)  # Frequency values
amplitudes = np.arange(0.5, 2.5, 0.5)   # Amplitude values

# Store trace visibility
visibility = []
for amp in amplitudes:
    for freq in frequencies:
        fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(
            visible=False,
            line=dict(width=2),
            name=f"ùúà = {freq}, A = {amp}",
            x=x,
            y=amp * np.sin(freq * x)
        ))
        visibility.append((amp, freq))

# Set an initial visible trace
fig.data[0].visible = True

# Create sliders
steps_freq = []
steps_amp = []

for i, freq in enumerate(frequencies):
    step = dict(
        method="update",
        args=[{"visible": [False] * len(fig.data)}],
        label=str(freq)
    )
    for j, (amp_val, freq_val) in enumerate(visibility):
        if freq_val == freq:
            step["args"][0]["visible"][j] = True
    steps_freq.append(step)

for i, amp in enumerate(amplitudes):
    step = dict(
        method="update",
        args=[{"visible": [False] * len(fig.data)}],
        label=str(amp)
    )
    for j, (amp_val, freq_val) in enumerate(visibility):
        if amp_val == amp:
            step["args"][0]["visible"][j] = True
    steps_amp.append(step)

sliders = [
    dict(
        active=0,
        currentvalue={"prefix": "Frequency: "},
        pad={"t": 50, "b": 30},  # Adjust vertical spacing
        y=1.15,  # Position above plot
        steps=steps_freq
    ),
    dict(
        active=0,
        currentvalue={"prefix": "Amplitude: "},
        pad={"t": 50, "b": 30},  # Adjust vertical spacing
        y=1.00,  # Position slightly below first slider
        steps=steps_amp
    )
]

fig.update_layout(sliders=sliders, title="Interactive Sine Wave with Two Sliders")

fig.show()
import plotly.graph_objects as go
import numpy as np

# Define parameter ranges
ŒîŒ≤_values = np.arange(-1, 1.04, 0.04)  # Step size of 0.04
Œîibar_values = np.arange(-0.5, 0.52, 0.02)  # Step size of 0.02

# Define fixed variables
ibar = 0
beta = 1
x = np.linspace(-.9, .9, 100)
xa = 0  # Initial product
ya = ibar  # Initial interest rate

# Create figure
fig = go.Figure()

# Generate traces for all slider combinations
for ŒîŒ≤ in ŒîŒ≤_values:
    for Œîibar in Œîibar_values:
        xa_equilib = xa - 0 + 0  # Œîi=0, y=0 for now
        ya_equilib = (ibar + Œîibar) + (beta + ŒîŒ≤) * xa_equilib
        
        TR = (ibar + Œîibar) + (beta + ŒîŒ≤) * x
        TR_ = ibar + (beta) * x

        fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(
            x=x, y=TR_, mode='lines',
            line=dict(color='silver', dash="dot"),
            visible=False, name=f"TR Base (ŒîŒ≤={ŒîŒ≤}, Œîibar={Œîibar})"
        ))
        fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(
            x=x, y=TR, mode='lines',
            line=dict(color="blue"),
            visible=False, name=f"TR Shifted (ŒîŒ≤={ŒîŒ≤}, Œîibar={Œîibar})"
        ))
        fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(
            x=[xa, xa], y=[-1, ya], mode='lines',
            line=dict(color='silver', dash="dot"),
            visible=False, showlegend=False
        ))
        fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(
            x=[xa_equilib], y=[ya_equilib], mode='markers',
            marker=dict(color="green", size=8),
            visible=False, name="Equilibrium"
        ))

# Set initial visibility
for i in range(4):  # First 4 traces belong to the initial ŒîŒ≤ and Œîibar
    fig.data[i].visible = True

# Create slider steps
steps_ŒîŒ≤ = []
steps_Œîibar = []

for i, ŒîŒ≤ in enumerate(ŒîŒ≤_values):
    step = dict(
        method="update",
        args=[{"visible": [False] * len(fig.data)}],
        label=f"{ŒîŒ≤:.2f}"
    )
    for j in range(len(Œîibar_values)):
        base_idx = (i * len(Œîibar_values) + j) * 4
        for k in range(4):  # Each set has 4 traces
            step["args"][0]["visible"][base_idx + k] = True
    steps_ŒîŒ≤.append(step)

for j, Œîibar in enumerate(Œîibar_values):
    step = dict(
        method="update",
        args=[{"visible": [False] * len(fig.data)}],
        label=f"{Œîibar:.2f}"
    )
    for i in range(len(ŒîŒ≤_values)):
        base_idx = (i * len(Œîibar_values) + j) * 4
        for k in range(4):
            step["args"][0]["visible"][base_idx + k] = True
    steps_Œîibar.append(step)

# Add sliders
fig.update_layout(
    sliders=[
        dict(
            active=25,
            currentvalue={"prefix": "ŒîŒ≤: "},
            pad={"t": 50},
            y=1.15,  # Positioning above the plot
            steps=steps_ŒîŒ≤
        ),
        dict(
            active=12,
            currentvalue={"prefix": "Œîibar: "},
            pad={"t": 50},
            y=1.00,  # Positioning below first slider
            steps=steps_Œîibar
        )
    ],
    title="Curva TR - Interactive",
    xaxis_title="Prodotto",
    yaxis_title="Tasso di Interesse",
    xaxis=dict(range=[-1, 1]),
    yaxis=dict(range=[-1, 1])
)

fig.show()
